Process Engineer

APACHE NITROGEN PRODUCTS, INC

- Saint David, AZ 85630

Summary
The Process Engineer is responsible for optimization and continuous improvement of Apache Nitrogen processes and process engineering support for capital improvement projects.
Key Responsibilities
Evaluate and offer recommendations for the day-to-day operation of the processing plants
Provide process troubleshooting, problem solving, and decision making, as well as root cause analysis of operations, maintenance and engineering issues
Assist with plant critical issues resolution
Stay abreast of industry changes and improvements
Provide process engineering support for capital projects
Develop and manage implementation of minor projects
Work within a team to implement systems to capture data to provide analysis and review of trends for efficiency, quality, safety, etc.
Engage Process and Maintenance Technicians in discussion regarding plant issues
Meet on a regular basis with the operations team to understand their needs
Utilize ANPI procedures for continuous improvement projects
Follow all PSM and other regulatory requirements
Monitor process controls
Assist in the education and training of other plant personnel on the Plant process, equipment, and unit operations. Develop associated operating procedures.
Assure a personal commitment to the Apache Safety, Health, & Environmental program
Other duties & responsibilities assigned
Qualifications
Bachelor’s Degree in Engineering, Chemical Engineering preferred.
Five years’ experience in a similar industry
Engineering in Training Certificate preferred
Professional Engineering Certificate preferred
Project management
